[src:archery-world-cup/archery-world-cup] The following table shows the total number of individual medals (including stage and finals).
[src:archery-world-cup/archery-world-cup] An **Indoor Archery World Cup** was inaugurated in 2010.
[src:archery-world-cup/archery-world-cup] It is played in the off-season (November to February), with fewer stages and the final competed in Las Vegas.
[src:archery-world-cup/archery-world-cup] In 2014, the stages were held in Marrakesh, Singapore and Telford.
[src:archery-world-cup/archery-world-cup] 2019-2020 Indoor Archery World Series have 6 qualification and one final stage.
[src:archery-world-cup/archery-world-cup] After 2018, the World Indoor Archery Championships were discontinued, leaving the Indoor Archery World Series as the premier championship in indoor archery.
